  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.9.23-stable\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : 8c2f271528f9cccf541c6ea1c022e98407f26872\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n1. creating geth new account without password.(0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2)\r\n2. geth attach rpc:http://127.0.0.1:8545\r\n3. personal.unlockAccount(eth.accounts[79]); \r\nUnlock account 0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2\r\nPassphrase:(Enter only)\r\ntrue\r\n4. There is no update features with web3.js. So I have to use geth CLI.\r\n5. geth account update 0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2\r\n6. Unlocking account 0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2| Attempt 1/3\r\nPassphrase:\r\n0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2\r\nAccount '0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2' unlocked.\r\nPlease give a new password. Do not forget this password.\r\nPassphrase: 12345678\r\nRepeat Passphrase: 12345678\r\n0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2\r\n7. finally password updated\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n1. creating geth new account without password.(0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2)\r\n2. geth attach rpc:http://127.0.0.1:8545\r\n3. personal.unlockAccount(eth.accounts[79]); \r\nUnlock account 0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2\r\nPassphrase:(Enter only)\r\ntrue\r\n4. There is no update features with web3.js. So I have to use geth CLI.\r\n5. geth account update 0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2\r\n6. Unlocking account 0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2| Attempt 1/3\r\nPassphrase:(Enter only)\r\nFatal: Failed to unlock account 0x2e34a48b0da51f55d569e0af7d0d6836ea8cd5a2 (no key for given address or file)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nI think geth CLI don't permit non-password input unlike Web3.js.\r\nOld geth permit sendTransactions without password. But now it is impossible. \r\nSo I can't send ETH coin  without updating some kind of password for old address.\r\n\r\nThis is critical bug. Help me!\r\n",
